CSS = cascading style sheets

1. There are 3 different ways in which 
we can apply CSS:

2. inline, internal, external

3. inline: we can apply CSS within 
the same line of the tag in HTML file.

#file index.html
<body style="background-color: black;">
<h1 style="color: whitesmoke;">My Website</h1>
    <p style="color: whitesmoke;">Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur </p>
    <p style="color: whitesmoke;">Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur </p>
    <p style="color: whitesmoke;">Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur </p>
    <p style="color: whitesmoke;">Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur </p>    
</body>

4. internal: we apply CSS within header tag.

#file index.html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Document</title>
    <style>
       body{
        background-color: black;
    }
        h1{
        color: rgb(214, 214, 72);
    }
        p{
        color: rgb(214, 214, 72);
    }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <h1>My Website</h1>
    <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur </p>
    <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur </p>
    <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur </p>
    <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur </p>    
</body>
</html> 

5. external: we will create CSS file and then link it to HTML file
by using a link tag <link>

#file index.html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Document</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <h1>My Website</h1>
    <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur </p>
    <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur </p>
    <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur </p>
    <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur </p>    
</body>
</html>

#file style.css
body{
    background-color: black;
}
h1{
    color: beige;
}
p{
    color: beige;
}


NOTE: 
1. In this sample, we select elements by tag name 
but we can select them by id (if they have), 
to select the element by id, 
we will use a # followed by the id name.

2. to apply CSS to a class, 
we will type . followed by the name of a class

tage name
#id name
.class name

3. We can apply one css file 
to more than one html file.





